WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:50.967 --> 00:00:52.927
[♪ eerie music plays]

3
00:04:03.743 --> 00:04:07.080
[clicking]

4
00:04:29.686 --> 00:04:30.937
[engine stops]

5
00:04:51.874 --> 00:04:55.712
Afternoon. sir. What exactly
seems to be the problem?

6
00:04:57.255 --> 00:04:58.756
[driver. distorted] Problem?

7
00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:02.051
You pulled over just then
when I was behind you.

8
00:05:03.177 --> 00:05:05.346
Maybe you're having
engine trouble. Is that it?

9
00:05:07.056 --> 00:05:08.099
[driver] No.

10
00:05:09.017 --> 00:05:10.226
I'm tired.

11
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:12.729
Thought I should rest.

12
00:05:15.106 --> 00:05:16.482
What brings you to Colby?

13
00:05:18.609 --> 00:05:19.944
[driver] Passing through.

14
00:05:21.446 --> 00:05:23.281
Sure. Okay.

15
00:05:24.615 --> 00:05:27.285
I'd like to take a look at
your license and registration.

16
00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:33.583
[driver]
Oh. uh... Have to find them.

17
00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:36.794
I'll be right here.

18
00:05:57.023 --> 00:05:58.107
Where you heading. lady?

19
00:05:59.067 --> 00:06:00.526
Home. What about you?

20
00:06:00.568 --> 00:06:02.111
Well. my mother always said

21
00:06:02.153 --> 00:06:04.238
you shouldn't judge a book
by its cover.

22
00:06:05.615 --> 00:06:07.575
but I'm guessing I'll be
running this gentleman in

23
00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:10.828
on drug charges
in all of about three minutes.

24
00:06:13.915 --> 00:06:15.166
You need me to stick around?

25
00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.090
No. I've got it.

26
00:06:22.131 --> 00:06:24.008
Make me a meat loaf.
What do you say?

27
00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:25.718
[chuckles] I'm sorry. honey.

28
00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:27.762
but I'll be sleeping
by the time you get in.

29
00:06:27.804 --> 00:06:29.222
[chuckles]

30
00:06:29.263 --> 00:06:30.681
You run the plates?

31
00:06:30.723 --> 00:06:32.642
I'm about to
if you'd let me do my job.

32
00:06:33.267 --> 00:06:35.269
-Love you.
-Love you.

33
00:06:45.363 --> 00:06:46.948
[engine starts]

34
00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:14.100
[sighs]

35
00:07:20.857 --> 00:07:23.234
I told you I need to see
your license and registration.

36
00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:28.072
Are you hard of hearing?

37
00:07:31.367 --> 00:07:33.286
Dispatch. this is car 14.

38
00:07:33.995 --> 00:07:35.580
-Do you even have a license?
-Go ahead. 14.

39
00:07:36.539 --> 00:07:38.666
I'm with 48 on that 10-81.

40
00:07:38.708 --> 00:07:40.501
Can you help me bring up
the latest bulletin

41
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:42.086
on the interstate homicides?

42
00:07:42.545 --> 00:07:45.715
Didn't Denver forward a list of
stolen vehicle plates from...

43
00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.634
-[gunshot]
-No!

44
00:08:05.693 --> 00:08:06.944
Oh. my God.

45
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:09.697
-Mike. Mike.
-[gurgles]

46
00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:11.908
Oh. my God. Mike. Okay.

47
00:08:11.949 --> 00:08:13.743
10-49. 10-49.

48
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:16.204
Shots fired. Trooper is down.

49
00:08:16.245 --> 00:08:19.373
[stammers] Shooter is
eastbound. eastbound on 28.

50
00:08:19.415 --> 00:08:21.292
Mile marker 79.

51
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.711
We need an ambulance.
It's Michael.

52
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.464
Okay. [breathing shakily]

53
00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:29.217
Honey. Honey. it's Jane.

54
00:08:29.759 --> 00:08:31.928
Everything's gonna be okay.
Okay?

55
00:08:31.969 --> 00:08:33.888
Everything's gonna be okay.
It is. It's...

56
00:08:33.930 --> 00:08:36.349
They're... They're
on their way. They're coming.

57
00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:38.684
They're coming right now.

58
00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:41.896
Michael.

59
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:45.149
Michael. please. please don't
do this. Please don't do this.

60
00:08:45.191 --> 00:08:46.817
No.
please don't do this right now.

61
00:08:46.859 --> 00:08:48.319
Please. They're coming.

62
00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:50.112
They're coming.
They're coming. Just...

63
00:08:50.154 --> 00:08:52.365
[sobbing]

64
00:08:52.406 --> 00:08:53.533
Please.

65
00:09:20.768 --> 00:09:21.894
Dad.

66
00:09:23.437 --> 00:09:25.815
He's... He's gone.

67
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:28.776
[sobbing]

68
00:09:38.828 --> 00:09:41.122
[news anchor on TV] It's
day five of a wave of terror

69
00:09:41.163 --> 00:09:43.291
and sudden
and unexpected violence

70
00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:46.085
that literally has
a stranglehold
on the American public.

71
00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:48.671
Across six states.
at least fifteen victims

72
00:09:48.713 --> 00:09:50.298
have met their fates

73
00:09:50.339 --> 00:09:52.049
at the hands
of the bloodthirsty killer

74
00:09:52.091 --> 00:09:53.759
that many are calling
"The Satanic Slasher."

75
00:09:53.801 --> 00:09:57.138
California. Nevada.
Utah. and Arizona.

76
00:09:57.179 --> 00:09:59.515
as well as New Mexico
and Colorado

77
00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:01.475
have seen a trail of bodies.

78
00:10:01.517 --> 00:10:05.479
dismemberments. decapitations
and mutilation.

79
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:08.733
Police now confirm that
satanic symbols
and graphic slurs

80
00:10:08.774 --> 00:10:10.359
were left at the scenes
of the murders.

81
00:10:10.401 --> 00:10:12.361
often written
in the victims' blood.

82
00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:15.031
In the next hour. we'll take
you inside the killer's mind

83
00:10:15.072 --> 00:10:16.949
as we speak with a psychiatrist

84
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:20.119
who's an expert in the
psychology of mass murderers.

85
00:10:31.464 --> 00:10:33.549
[breathing heavily]

86
00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:56.238
[engine sputtering]

87
00:11:05.039 --> 00:11:07.083
[♪ ominous music plays]

88
00:11:55.172 --> 00:11:57.425
[man and woman
speaking indistinctly]

89
00:12:05.349 --> 00:12:06.809
[both chuckle]

90
00:12:06.851 --> 00:12:08.185
[woman]
Oh. yeah? Do you want to trade?

91
00:12:08.227 --> 00:12:09.478
[man] Um. I will
at the house tomorrow.

92
00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:10.855
[woman]
Oh. okay. tomorrow. Okay.

93
00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:13.566
-Okay. bye. [chuckles]
-[man] Good night.

94
00:12:13.607 --> 00:12:15.526
-[woman] Get home safe.
-You too.

95
00:12:33.377 --> 00:12:34.962
[engine starts]

96
00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:52.146
[♪ ominous music playing]

97
00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:56.233
[woman screams]

98
00:12:56.275 --> 00:12:58.360
[muffled screaming. grunting]

99
00:13:00.738 --> 00:13:02.448
[screaming. grunting stop]

100
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:43.572
[people speaking
indistinctly. muffled]

101
00:13:52.331 --> 00:13:53.415
[sighs]

102
00:14:03.092 --> 00:14:04.301
Anything?

103
00:14:06.554 --> 00:14:08.639
He headed south
towards Dodge City

104
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:10.099
and abandoned the sedan.

105
00:14:10.724 --> 00:14:12.560
We found another victim.

106
00:14:13.102 --> 00:14:14.186
-A woman.
-[breathes shakily]

107
00:14:14.228 --> 00:14:15.813
He took her ID. everything.

108
00:14:15.855 --> 00:14:18.148
so there's... there's no way
to identify her yet.

109
00:14:18.732 --> 00:14:20.401
There's no telling
what he's driving now.

110
00:14:23.028 --> 00:14:25.739
There's a potential
emotional undercurrent here

111
00:14:25.781 --> 00:14:27.533
that we haven't
touched upon yet.

112
00:14:28.075 --> 00:14:29.660
and that is survivor's guilt.

113
00:14:30.411 --> 00:14:33.372
As a woman
in a predominantly male field.

114
00:14:33.414 --> 00:14:37.626
a field where overt masculinity
and intimidating
physical presence.

115
00:14:37.668 --> 00:14:41.088
even aggressive demeanor.
can be considered virtues.

116
00:14:41.547 --> 00:14:43.507
you may have already
been experiencing

117
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:45.759
occasional feelings
of inadequacy.

118
00:14:46.218 --> 00:14:48.470
whether you recognize them
as such or not.

119
00:14:49.597 --> 00:14:52.808
Which could add further weight
to the emotional baggage
you take away

120
00:14:52.850 --> 00:14:55.311
from having been a witness
to the death of your husband.

121
00:14:55.978 --> 00:14:59.398
A death for which
you seem wrongly
to be blaming yourself.

122
00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:00.524
at least in part.

123
00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.402
The reality of the situation.

124
00:15:04.111 --> 00:15:06.822
what I hope to help you
come to grips with is.

125
00:15:07.573 --> 00:15:09.283
no matter how many times

126
00:15:09.325 --> 00:15:12.328
you replay what happened
back in your mind.

127
00:15:13.454 --> 00:15:15.372
the outcome is inescapable.

128
00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:18.459
You must find a way
to begin accepting that.

129
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:21.754
Are we done here?

130
00:15:21.795 --> 00:15:23.964
-We are. aren't we?
-Officer Archer...

131
00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:27.134
I'm only here 'cause
this is mandatory. I told you.

132
00:15:28.010 --> 00:15:29.094
You've had your hour.

133
00:15:29.136 --> 00:15:31.430
An hour is barely a beginning.

134
00:15:31.472 --> 00:15:34.850
It hasn't even been 48 hours
since you buried your husband.

135
00:15:34.892 --> 00:15:36.435
-[breathes heavily]
-Without question.

136
00:15:36.477 --> 00:15:37.978
I will be recommending
further therapy and--

137
00:15:38.020 --> 00:15:40.314
I don't know what I'm gonna do
without him.

138
00:15:40.356 --> 00:15:42.191
There.

139
00:15:42.232 --> 00:15:43.525
Now you know.

140
00:15:44.693 --> 00:15:47.404
They tell me I've got to keep
coming here. then I will.

141
00:15:47.446 --> 00:15:49.198
otherwise your hour's up.

142
00:15:49.239 --> 00:15:50.950
Thank you. Goodbye.

143
00:16:01.126 --> 00:16:02.628
[water running]

144
00:16:07.383 --> 00:16:09.134
[breathing heavily]

145
00:16:16.058 --> 00:16:17.226
-[grunts]
-[gasps]

146
00:16:18.727 --> 00:16:20.145
[gasps. pants]

147
00:16:20.187 --> 00:16:21.897
[reporter on TV]
...dismembered bodies

148
00:16:21.939 --> 00:16:23.732
discovered a hundred miles
east of Kansas City.

149
00:16:24.692 --> 00:16:27.903
Seven people have been killed
in the state of Illinois alone.

150
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:29.571
It's believed by many
that the Slasher

151
00:16:29.613 --> 00:16:32.324
is heading north
towards the Canadian border.

152
00:16:32.366 --> 00:16:34.952
Authorities are cautioning
those living
in the northern Midwest

153
00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:39.373
that the Slasher
may have already crossed
into Wisconsin or Michigan.

154
00:16:43.085 --> 00:16:44.586
[man] Whenever you put
that uniform on.

155
00:16:44.628 --> 00:16:46.088
you might as well
become another person.

156
00:16:46.130 --> 00:16:47.673
[sighs]

157
00:16:48.924 --> 00:16:51.218
Your heart and soul
belongs to the KHP.

158
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:53.887
That's who you are. Jane.

159
00:16:53.929 --> 00:16:55.097
Who you've always been.

160
00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:57.725
Look who's talking.

161
00:16:57.766 --> 00:16:59.476
Yeah. well. at least you know
I'm speaking from experience.

162
00:17:01.979 --> 00:17:04.231
There is such a thing as

163
00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:05.733
disappearing into that uniform.

164
00:17:06.358 --> 00:17:09.361
or thinking that it's
some kind of suit of armor.

165
00:17:10.112 --> 00:17:11.405
which it isn't.

166
00:17:11.864 --> 00:17:13.490
I'll be back soon. I promise.

167
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:15.534
Took provisional leave.
two weeks.

168
00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.537
Mike dying wasn't your fault.

169
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:19.913
[Jane sighs]

170
00:17:21.749 --> 00:17:23.042
[father] Listen to me.

171
00:17:23.083 --> 00:17:24.543
Nothing that
you could have done

172
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:25.878
that would have
changed anything.

173
00:17:27.004 --> 00:17:28.172
nothing you could have
done differently

174
00:17:28.213 --> 00:17:29.506
that would have saved him.

175
00:17:29.548 --> 00:17:30.841
Yeah. I know.

176
00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:33.260
So... So what then? [stammers]

177
00:17:33.302 --> 00:17:36.680
I mean. look. you do realize
it's crazy what you're doing?

178
00:17:36.722 --> 00:17:39.933
He's not the one I'm trying
to save. all right?

179
00:17:42.061 --> 00:17:44.688
Since... [sighs]
...four days ago.

180
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:46.523
four days that have felt
like a lifetime.

181
00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.484
I have thought about one thing.

182
00:17:49.777 --> 00:17:50.861
The shot.

183
00:17:51.737 --> 00:17:53.155
The shot I had...

184
00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:56.366
and what I wouldn't give
to have it back.

185
00:17:58.243 --> 00:17:59.453
'Cause you're right.

186
00:18:00.162 --> 00:18:01.747
nothing'll bring Mike back.

187
00:18:02.998 --> 00:18:04.166
So what's left?

188
00:18:06.001 --> 00:18:08.253
Another shot... another chance.

189
00:18:08.295 --> 00:18:11.131
Just one bullet could save
however many lives.

190
00:18:11.173 --> 00:18:13.675
and Mike gets to rest in peace.

191
00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:16.804
And I don't know.
maybe I get to sleep at night.

192
00:18:16.845 --> 00:18:17.888
Look. [sighs]

193
00:18:19.765 --> 00:18:22.101
-You'll never find him.
-I don't have to find him.

194
00:18:22.643 --> 00:18:25.104
Sooner or later.
his luck will run out
and he'll get boxed in.

195
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:27.898
And when that happens.
all I want is another shot.

196
00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:30.651
-Hey. Jane. just listen--
-Dad. I'm done talking.

197
00:18:31.235 --> 00:18:32.820
You know me.

198
00:18:32.861 --> 00:18:35.072
Tell me again not to go.
you think that'll stop me?

199
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:42.704
Keep your gun and badge
with you at all times.

200
00:18:46.917 --> 00:18:49.545
Pointless as it is.
what you're doing...

201
00:18:52.005 --> 00:18:53.423
I'll admit.

202
00:18:54.675 --> 00:18:56.176
if I were you.

203
00:18:57.261 --> 00:18:59.888
I believe I'd also need to
find that out for myself.

204
00:19:05.978 --> 00:19:07.729
[caller on radio]
The time for exploring

205
00:19:07.771 --> 00:19:10.983
life's sinful perversions
is now.

206
00:19:11.775 --> 00:19:13.777
The planet rapers
have got it right.

207
00:19:13.819 --> 00:19:17.281
Earth is meant to have
our seed spilt upon it.

208
00:19:17.322 --> 00:19:19.241
and to be trod upon
and pillaged.

209
00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:22.703
Forcibly violated
and voraciously consumed.

210
00:19:23.245 --> 00:19:27.040
I give thanks
to His Infernal Majesty

211
00:19:27.082 --> 00:19:29.251
and his pharmaceutical empire

212
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:31.295
for their creation
of painkillers

213
00:19:31.336 --> 00:19:35.174
and their almighty
erection medications.

214
00:19:35.215 --> 00:19:37.926
For there is
no greater foretelling

215
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:41.471
that humankind is heading
in the right direction.

216
00:19:47.853 --> 00:19:49.062
[grunts]

217
00:19:49.104 --> 00:19:51.148
[♪ pop music playing on radio]

218
00:19:52.941 --> 00:19:56.737
[caller]
Join me. for we will rise.

219
00:19:56.778 --> 00:19:58.947
Discerning believers
can find us

220
00:19:58.989 --> 00:20:02.201
in the classified section
of The National Tribune.

221
00:20:02.242 --> 00:20:04.745
if you've got the dedication.

222
00:20:04.786 --> 00:20:06.914
[host] Well. thank you.
Mr. Pendleton.

223
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:09.124
It's always very
illuminating for--

224
00:20:38.487 --> 00:20:40.280
[straining]

225
00:20:47.913 --> 00:20:49.122
No. No.

226
00:20:49.164 --> 00:20:51.041
-N-- [grunts]
-[gasps]

227
00:20:52.918 --> 00:20:53.961
[volume fades]

228
00:20:54.002 --> 00:20:55.754
[breathing shakily]

229
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:01.468
Charlie?

230
00:21:05.180 --> 00:21:06.306
[object thuds]

231
00:21:12.145 --> 00:21:14.898
[gasping. breathing shakily]

232
00:21:23.198 --> 00:21:25.075
[whimpering. panting]

233
00:21:33.166 --> 00:21:34.793
Help! Help me!

234
00:21:34.835 --> 00:21:36.545
-[horn honks]
-Help! Please!

235
00:21:38.463 --> 00:21:40.549
Help! Help me!

236
00:21:42.009 --> 00:21:43.135
[tires screech]

237
00:22:33.894 --> 00:22:36.855
Well. I have our case files
for Topeka. Yeah.

238
00:22:38.148 --> 00:22:40.359
Uh. in the spirit
of cooperation.

239
00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:41.985
maybe you could
let me take a look

240
00:22:42.027 --> 00:22:43.737
at what you've got
on the Kit Carson killings.

241
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:48.867
Yeah. Well. as a professional
courtesy. I was hoping that...

242
00:22:51.912 --> 00:22:52.954
[sucks teeth]

243
00:22:53.830 --> 00:22:55.957
Is there anyone else
that I can speak to?

244
00:22:56.875 --> 00:22:58.502
And that's what my point is.

245
00:22:59.169 --> 00:23:01.421
Belief is not enough
to solve this case.

246
00:23:01.463 --> 00:23:02.881
[Jane]
Yeah. Well. any information

247
00:23:02.923 --> 00:23:04.091
would be really.
really helpful.

248
00:23:04.633 --> 00:23:06.885
Okay. Well. maybe
I could speak to him.

249
00:23:06.927 --> 00:23:08.178
When will he next be in?

250
00:23:09.137 --> 00:23:11.056
Anything would be helpful.

251
00:23:11.681 --> 00:23:14.851
Any information on the Slasher
killings in Las Vegas or--

252
00:23:16.812 --> 00:23:20.273
Okay. Well. maybe
I can leave my number
in case you change your mind.

253
00:23:21.191 --> 00:23:22.275
Thank you.

254
00:23:24.361 --> 00:23:26.530
Thanks for nothing. [sighs]

255
00:23:26.571 --> 00:23:28.198
Hate you all.

256
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:31.368
[sighs]

257
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.245
[Slasher] I want to put in
a classified ad.

258
00:23:34.538 --> 00:23:35.997
How much is it for Sunday?

259
00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:38.667
The national ad.

260
00:23:41.753 --> 00:23:43.422
Will you take
a credit card number?

261
00:23:46.675 --> 00:23:51.430
First line
of the ad is. "M N O."

262
00:23:54.850 --> 00:23:58.270
Capital "M." space.
Capital "N." space.

263
00:23:58.311 --> 00:23:59.563
Capital "O."

264
00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:02.357
Under that.

265
00:24:03.191 --> 00:24:05.152
"To those who also share faith.

266
00:24:06.361 --> 00:24:08.280
Seeking our mutual friend.

267
00:24:09.406 --> 00:24:10.740
Need help.

268
00:24:11.992 --> 00:24:13.076
Please reply."

269
00:24:27.048 --> 00:24:28.425
Let Chicago know.

270
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:29.718
So long as they're kept
in the loop.

271
00:24:29.759 --> 00:24:31.219
maybe they'll stay
out of our hair.

272
00:24:31.261 --> 00:24:33.430
DC gets CC'd on everything.
those SOBs.

273
00:24:33.472 --> 00:24:35.265
Okay. right now I need
two equally important things

274
00:24:35.307 --> 00:24:36.808
brought to me
in the next 15 minutes.

275
00:24:36.850 --> 00:24:39.060
The entire forensics workup
on the Slasher

276
00:24:39.102 --> 00:24:40.228
and a chicken salad sandwich.

277
00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.022
Excuse me. Are you Agent Zolan?

278
00:24:43.356 --> 00:24:45.108
Uh. sorry.
I was looking for you.

279
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:47.736
And you are?

280
00:24:48.361 --> 00:24:50.989
Officer Jane Archer
of the Kansas state police.

281
00:24:51.781 --> 00:24:54.201
I was told you're heading up
the Slasher investigation.

282
00:24:54.910 --> 00:24:55.952
May I?

283
00:24:57.871 --> 00:24:59.915
If you don't mind. I'd like to
look over your shoulder

284
00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:01.291
for a day or two.

285
00:25:01.333 --> 00:25:03.376
I realize it's
an unusual request.

286
00:25:03.418 --> 00:25:04.628
You're joking. right?

287
00:25:04.669 --> 00:25:06.379
[Jane]
Pretty serious. actually.

288
00:25:06.421 --> 00:25:09.466
You know. the trooper
that was murdered in Kansas.

289
00:25:09.508 --> 00:25:10.759
he was my husband.

290
00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:12.886
I was with him when he died.

291
00:25:15.972 --> 00:25:17.599
Is it so much to ask. just...

292
00:25:18.225 --> 00:25:19.643
help me fill in the blanks?

293
00:25:21.102 --> 00:25:22.646
[Zolan] I feel for you.

294
00:25:23.188 --> 00:25:25.148
We're all sorry for your loss.

295
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:26.566
The KHP's loss.

296
00:25:27.984 --> 00:25:29.569
But with due respect.

297
00:25:30.111 --> 00:25:32.155
I don't appreciate
having my arm twisted.

298
00:25:38.703 --> 00:25:40.580
What are you even looking for.
Trooper?

299
00:25:43.667 --> 00:25:45.335
Take a nickel's worth
of free advice.

300
00:25:46.711 --> 00:25:47.754
go home.

301
00:26:15.532 --> 00:26:18.577
[breathing heavily]

302
00:26:41.683 --> 00:26:42.726
[chuckles]

303
00:27:00.452 --> 00:27:01.911
[whimpers]

304
00:27:05.624 --> 00:27:07.042
[phone buzzing]

305
00:27:10.503 --> 00:27:11.713
Hello.

306
00:27:11.755 --> 00:27:13.214
[woman] Yeah. hello.

307
00:27:13.256 --> 00:27:15.383
Is this Trooper Archer?
Jane Archer?

308
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.802
Yeah. who is this?

309
00:27:17.844 --> 00:27:19.846
This is Agent Becky Collins.

310
00:27:19.888 --> 00:27:22.891
We crossed paths at the FBI
field office earlier.

311
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:25.560
I'm thinking maybe
we should talk.

312
00:27:26.686 --> 00:27:29.105
[♪ country music playing
on speakers]

313
00:27:29.147 --> 00:27:30.523
-[bartender] There you go.
-Thanks.

314
00:27:39.032 --> 00:27:40.825
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

315
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:44.496
I really appreciate
you meeting with me.

316
00:27:44.537 --> 00:27:46.748
Yeah. Well. next round
is definitely on you.

317
00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:49.626
If Zolan knew I was walking
you through this. he'd. uh...

318
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:52.587
Screw it.

319
00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:55.632
As we know. the first killings
were 16 days ago.

320
00:27:56.174 --> 00:27:58.718
Death Valley Junction.
A tiny place.

321
00:27:58.760 --> 00:28:01.012
He dismembered the Durk's
Paint shopkeeper there.

322
00:28:02.639 --> 00:28:04.683
Stole money.
credit card numbers.

323
00:28:04.724 --> 00:28:06.226
tools. clothing. food.

324
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:10.188
The victims he chooses. there
are those of pure opportunity

325
00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:12.065
and those he takes
something specific from.

326
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:14.234
like the pharmacist
from Colorado.

327
00:28:14.275 --> 00:28:17.195
Yeah. he'll kill for
painkillers and psychotropics.

328
00:28:17.237 --> 00:28:19.698
Percocet. Percodan. OxyContin.

329
00:28:19.739 --> 00:28:21.324
We don't think he's dealing.

330
00:28:21.366 --> 00:28:23.535
He's taking these drugs
himself. All of them.

331
00:28:24.077 --> 00:28:26.579
And the gun shop
in. uh. Nevada. was it?

332
00:28:26.621 --> 00:28:28.581
That's him.
He broke in after hours.

333
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:32.502
Got away with
at least one pistol.
a shotgun. plenty of ammo

334
00:28:32.544 --> 00:28:34.546
and the shop's owner
was a collector.

335
00:28:34.587 --> 00:28:37.173
He had a secret stash
of hand grenades.

336
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:38.299
Now. all missing.

337
00:28:38.341 --> 00:28:40.719
-Jesus.
-Mm-hmm. Yeah.

338
00:28:40.760 --> 00:28:44.222
And. um. the library
in Cedar City. Utah.

339
00:28:44.264 --> 00:28:47.225
He killed the security guard
and the librarian.

340
00:28:47.726 --> 00:28:49.936
Yeah. We got that surveillance.

341
00:28:52.188 --> 00:28:54.441
What did he want
from a public library

342
00:28:54.482 --> 00:28:56.359
that he couldn't get
off the Internet?

343
00:28:56.401 --> 00:28:59.028
[Becky] Well. if there's one
thing the FBI still does well.

344
00:28:59.070 --> 00:29:00.822
it's track the Internet.

345
00:29:00.864 --> 00:29:02.532
and he's not on it.

346
00:29:02.574 --> 00:29:05.618
He took exactly two books
from a set of encyclopedias.

347
00:29:05.660 --> 00:29:06.911
"N" and "T."

348
00:29:06.953 --> 00:29:07.996
"N" and "T."

349
00:29:09.914 --> 00:29:12.000
His mission.
if he even has a mission.

350
00:29:12.041 --> 00:29:14.252
has him heading east
from motel to motel.

351
00:29:14.294 --> 00:29:16.129
Sometimes spending whole days
in one place.

352
00:29:16.963 --> 00:29:18.923
How do you know
he's been staying at motels?

353
00:29:18.965 --> 00:29:21.718
I assumed he'd been living
in his vehicle.

354
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:24.721
If you want. I can show you.

355
00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:44.574
He was here three days ago.
Three days after Kansas.

356
00:29:44.616 --> 00:29:46.242
Checked in
in the dead of night.

357
00:29:46.284 --> 00:29:47.619
On foot. paid cash.

358
00:29:48.077 --> 00:29:50.038
Hotel clerk was a total stoner.

359
00:29:50.079 --> 00:29:51.539
Couldn't give a description.

360
00:29:51.581 --> 00:29:54.125
Didn't even have him register.
Worthless.

361
00:29:54.626 --> 00:29:56.377
Middle of the next day.
the maid ignored

362
00:29:56.419 --> 00:29:57.962
the "Do not disturb" sign
on the doorknob

363
00:29:58.004 --> 00:30:00.965
or didn't see it somehow.
let herself in.

364
00:30:11.142 --> 00:30:12.977
[♪ ominous music plays]

365
00:30:14.479 --> 00:30:16.606
[Becky] He used an axe.
cut her in half.

366
00:30:18.024 --> 00:30:20.652
This seems to have gotten
his creative juices flowing.

367
00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:23.863
This is how he leaves
all the crime scenes.

368
00:30:26.491 --> 00:30:28.618
[Jane] "Open the gates."

369
00:30:30.870 --> 00:30:34.082
Our analysts say
he's obsessed with having
his achievements seen.

370
00:30:37.293 --> 00:30:38.461
Can I use your computer?

371
00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:44.050
Take a look at this.

372
00:30:44.092 --> 00:30:46.344
It's from those murders
in Harrisburg. Pennsylvania.

373
00:30:46.386 --> 00:30:47.762
Church killings. years ago.

374
00:30:47.804 --> 00:30:50.640
He was a satanist.
Richard Reeves.

375
00:30:50.682 --> 00:30:53.184
Richard Joshua Reeves.
He killed 13 people.

376
00:30:53.226 --> 00:30:54.686
Similar profile.

377
00:30:54.727 --> 00:30:56.604
We're aware.

378
00:30:56.646 --> 00:30:59.440
Those kind of satanic symbols
and phrases do tend to overlap.

379
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:02.402
but our guy.
he's not really copycatting.

380
00:31:02.443 --> 00:31:05.280
Reeves was a mass murderer.
not serial.

381
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:07.240
[Jane sighs]

382
00:31:07.282 --> 00:31:09.284
Maybe an admirer
of Reeves. at least.

383
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:11.995
Inspired by him.

384
00:31:12.954 --> 00:31:15.582
Okay. judging by the distances
he's been traveling.

385
00:31:15.623 --> 00:31:18.793
in the next day or two. this
is where he'll actually be.

386
00:31:18.835 --> 00:31:21.754
Somewhere between
Columbus. Ohio.
and Wheeling. West Virginia.

387
00:31:21.796 --> 00:31:24.841
110 miles. 25 exits.
give or take.

388
00:31:25.508 --> 00:31:28.011
This is the best chance anyone
has of running him down.

389
00:31:29.929 --> 00:31:32.390
Well. I don't know if
it's right to wish you luck.

390
00:31:32.432 --> 00:31:35.101
so I'll just say be careful.

391
00:31:36.978 --> 00:31:38.521
Thanks for sticking
your neck out.

392
00:31:38.563 --> 00:31:41.065
I wish there was some way
I could repay the favor.

393
00:31:42.108 --> 00:31:43.610
I'll pass your theories along.

394
00:31:43.651 --> 00:31:45.737
[scoffs]
For all the good that'll do.

395
00:31:53.536 --> 00:31:54.579
[sighs]

396
00:32:02.462 --> 00:32:04.714
I'm not allowed
to be telling you
what I'm about to tell you.

397
00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:07.300
There's a small construction
and demolition company

398
00:32:07.342 --> 00:32:08.426
near Kansas City.

399
00:32:09.302 --> 00:32:11.346
A quantity of explosives
were stolen.

400
00:32:12.096 --> 00:32:13.014
Explosives?

401
00:32:13.056 --> 00:32:14.307
Dynamite.

402
00:32:14.766 --> 00:32:18.144
About 20 pounds or so
of old-school. volatile TNT.

403
00:32:18.186 --> 00:32:20.855
Enough to do
significant damage.

404
00:32:23.232 --> 00:32:24.817
[reporter on TV]
Manson and "The Family."

405
00:32:24.859 --> 00:32:27.195
as the cult members
called themselves.

406
00:32:27.236 --> 00:32:30.406
killed seven people
in the infamous
Tate-LaBianca murders of 1969.

407
00:32:30.448 --> 00:32:33.826
Messages were left written
on the walls in blood.

408
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:37.497
Devil worship was also
the motive 20 years ago.

409
00:32:37.538 --> 00:32:41.501
when teenager
Richard Joshua Reeves
committed the grisly killings

410
00:32:41.542 --> 00:32:44.253
at Christ Cross Church
in Harrisburg. Pennsylvania.

411
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:47.090
Reeves murdered 13 hostages
inside the church.

412
00:32:47.131 --> 00:32:48.716
including a priest.

413
00:32:48.758 --> 00:32:50.677
while performing
what authorities described

414
00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:52.804
as a ritualistic black mass.

415
00:32:52.845 --> 00:32:54.889
[breathing shakily]

416
00:32:59.644 --> 00:33:02.855
[♪ ominous music playing]

417
00:33:05.608 --> 00:33:07.986
[caller 2 on radio] Slasher.
killing all those people.

418
00:33:08.027 --> 00:33:11.030
When this is over. you wanna
know who's gonna be behind it?

419
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:12.532
The government.

420
00:33:12.573 --> 00:33:14.617
I read on 8chan
how our government.

421
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:17.704
they've been keeping criminals
in secret military prisons

422
00:33:17.745 --> 00:33:19.539
for doing experiments on.

423
00:33:19.580 --> 00:33:21.749
Now one of those criminals
finally escaped.

424
00:33:22.458 --> 00:33:24.335
[radio DJ]
Z100.5. we'll begin another

425
00:33:24.377 --> 00:33:27.797
commercial-free block
of smooth jazz in a moment.

426
00:33:27.839 --> 00:33:30.425
But first. the Satanic Slasher.

427
00:33:36.973 --> 00:33:38.391
[bells tolling]

428
00:33:42.437 --> 00:33:44.439
[passersby
chatting indistinctly]

429
00:34:17.597 --> 00:34:18.681
Hello?

430
00:34:23.686 --> 00:34:24.771
Can I help you?

431
00:34:40.203 --> 00:34:41.621
[sighs]

432
00:34:43.414 --> 00:34:44.457
I'm listening.

433
00:34:46.167 --> 00:34:48.086
[Slasher]
I've always liked priests.

434
00:34:49.712 --> 00:34:51.380
When I was just a young boy.

435
00:34:52.256 --> 00:34:55.927
my priest.
he took me under his wing.

436
00:34:57.720 --> 00:34:59.097
You could say

437
00:35:00.056 --> 00:35:02.558
that he made me into the man
that I am today.

438
00:35:02.600 --> 00:35:04.936
Oh. that's good. my son.
Very good.

439
00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:07.688
And have you come to.
uh. confess?

440
00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:12.401
-Not exactly.
-Pardon me?

441
00:35:12.985 --> 00:35:16.155
[choking]

442
00:35:17.740 --> 00:35:19.659
[grunts. panting]

443
00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:21.369
[screams]

444
00:35:21.410 --> 00:35:23.454
[slurping]

445
00:36:14.297 --> 00:36:16.924
-[clears throat]
-Congratulations.

446
00:36:20.803 --> 00:36:22.638
Oh. Thank you.

447
00:36:25.975 --> 00:36:28.436
That reminds me. um.

448
00:36:28.477 --> 00:36:30.313
could I get a glass of milk.
please?

449
00:36:33.941 --> 00:36:35.359
Thank you.

450
00:36:49.081 --> 00:36:50.416
[♪ black metal playing
on laptop]

451
00:37:17.485 --> 00:37:19.070
Jesus.

452
00:37:19.111 --> 00:37:20.613
[narrator on laptop]
Richard Joshua Reeves

453
00:37:20.655 --> 00:37:23.074
slaughtered the 13 men
and women

454
00:37:23.115 --> 00:37:25.868
he briefly held hostage
inside the church
that March afternoon.

455
00:37:25.910 --> 00:37:29.038
He claimed that
human sacrifice was necessary

456
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:32.375
to. quote. "fulfill
his obligation to Satan."

457
00:37:32.959 --> 00:37:35.294
In a coordinated siege
upon the church.

458
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:37.380
Harrisburg police officers

459
00:37:37.421 --> 00:37:40.007
managed to capture
Reeves alive.

460
00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:43.094
In 2004.
facing a death sentence.

461
00:37:43.135 --> 00:37:45.179
Reeves finally met his end

462
00:37:45.221 --> 00:37:48.933
when he was shot and killed
while attacking a prison guard

463
00:37:48.975 --> 00:37:51.102
in the federal penitentiary
where he was held.

464
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:55.564
We're asking all the major
East Coast hotel chains

465
00:37:55.606 --> 00:37:56.857
to help us find the Slasher.

466
00:37:56.899 --> 00:37:58.567
Yes. sir.

467
00:37:58.609 --> 00:38:00.486
The suspect is almost
certainly a white male.

468
00:38:02.071 --> 00:38:04.073
Above average height.
stocky build.

469
00:38:04.115 --> 00:38:06.409
will be traveling alone.
pays in cash.

470
00:38:06.450 --> 00:38:10.788
Whatever you do.
do not confront this man.

471
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:12.540
If you have suspicions

472
00:38:12.581 --> 00:38:13.708
about a guest
you feel fits the description.

473
00:38:13.749 --> 00:38:15.042
call 911.

474
00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:18.254
Afternoon. sir. Officer Archer.

475
00:38:19.088 --> 00:38:22.300
I'm sorry to trouble you. but
we'd actually like some help

476
00:38:22.341 --> 00:38:24.635
watching out for
the interstate killer.

477
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.678
The Slasher.

478
00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:27.513
Oh.

479
00:38:27.555 --> 00:38:29.557
What little information
we have. I'd like to run by you

480
00:38:29.682 --> 00:38:31.934
in case any of your guests
match the profile.

481
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:35.021
He'd be a white male. alone.
paid in cash most likely.

482
00:38:35.980 --> 00:38:38.274
Police have made it sound like

483
00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:40.234
he's likely not gonna
come around here.

484
00:38:40.276 --> 00:38:42.153
Yeah. uh. I'm starting to think

485
00:38:42.194 --> 00:38:43.779
they're probably right
about that actually.

486
00:38:43.821 --> 00:38:45.823
And I wasn't working
the desk last night

487
00:38:45.865 --> 00:38:47.366
so I don't know
how helpful I can be.

488
00:38:47.408 --> 00:38:48.784
I...

489
00:38:48.826 --> 00:38:50.161
I can check the register.

490
00:38:50.202 --> 00:38:51.787
We still have
our guests sign in.

491
00:38:54.832 --> 00:38:56.625
There's no one staying alone.

492
00:38:56.667 --> 00:38:59.420
All right. Uh. maybe I'll just
leave you my number.

493
00:38:59.462 --> 00:39:01.005
Um. thanks for your time.

494
00:39:01.881 --> 00:39:03.424
Oh. There's one gentleman.

495
00:39:03.466 --> 00:39:05.468
Uh...

496
00:39:05.509 --> 00:39:08.179
Checked in last night. Alone.

497
00:39:09.263 --> 00:39:10.931
Uh. Mr. Reeves.

498
00:39:10.973 --> 00:39:12.767
[♪ ominous music plays]

499
00:39:12.808 --> 00:39:14.310
What did you say?

500
00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:17.063
Uh. Reeves.
Late last night. R.J. Reeves.

501
00:39:17.563 --> 00:39:19.190
-May I... May I look at that?
-Yep.

502
00:39:23.027 --> 00:39:24.070
Room 105?

503
00:39:24.528 --> 00:39:27.698
Go down the hall.
make a left. Outside.

504
00:39:28.240 --> 00:39:29.909
Okay. I'm gonna need
that key. sir.

505
00:39:32.787 --> 00:39:35.873
Okay. you call the police. you
tell them the Slasher is here.

506
00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:38.292
This is not a prank call.
This is for real.

507
00:39:39.293 --> 00:39:40.586
Call them now.

508
00:39:49.512 --> 00:39:51.555
[breathing shakily]

509
00:40:18.332 --> 00:40:19.667
[door creaks]

510
00:40:19.708 --> 00:40:22.253
[mother chuckles.
speaks indistinctly]

511
00:40:22.795 --> 00:40:25.339
[mother. child chattering]

