00:59:58.052 --> 01:00:00.138
[muffled panting. moaning]

774
01:00:17.030 --> 01:00:18.031
[muffled scream]

775
01:00:19.324 --> 01:00:20.491
[man on floor]
Whoa. whoa. wait!

776
01:00:21.743 --> 01:00:22.869
[woman groans]

777
01:00:24.704 --> 01:00:26.122
[screams]

778
01:00:30.376 --> 01:00:32.337
No. no. no.

779
01:00:32.378 --> 01:00:33.796
[grunting]

780
01:00:33.838 --> 01:00:34.881
[cries out]

781
01:00:38.676 --> 01:00:40.011
[woman panting]

782
01:00:41.846 --> 01:00:43.139
[Pendleton] Pazuzu.

783
01:00:43.598 --> 01:00:45.558
Pazuzu. be gone.

784
01:00:46.267 --> 01:00:47.393
[woman grunts]

785
01:00:50.188 --> 01:00:51.522
Pazuzu.

786
01:00:52.190 --> 01:00:53.900
Pazuzu. be gone.

787
01:00:55.193 --> 01:00:56.903
They are seven.

788
01:00:57.570 --> 01:00:59.238
They are seven.

789
01:01:01.949 --> 01:01:03.993
[♪ jarring. discordant music
playing]

790
01:01:49.789 --> 01:01:51.082
[fire roaring]

791
01:01:52.834 --> 01:01:54.377
[flames crackling]

792
01:02:22.071 --> 01:02:23.114
[gunshot whistles]

793
01:02:26.325 --> 01:02:27.535
[♪ tense music playing]

794
01:02:50.433 --> 01:02:51.559
[tires screeching]

795
01:03:01.569 --> 01:03:03.070
[tires screeching]

796
01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:08.993
Fuck! Fuck!

797
01:03:09.035 --> 01:03:11.579
[whimpering. panting]

798
01:03:11.621 --> 01:03:13.498
-[panting continues]
-[engine sputtering]

799
01:03:16.959 --> 01:03:19.003
[sputtering slows. stops]

800
01:03:19.045 --> 01:03:21.088
[firefighters chattering
indistinctly]

801
01:03:23.966 --> 01:03:26.052
[Jane] What I had.
I gave to you Feds

802
01:03:26.093 --> 01:03:28.387
and to everyone and anyone
who would listen.

803
01:03:28.429 --> 01:03:30.848
I gave you everything.
Everything.

804
01:03:30.890 --> 01:03:32.558
So. where the fuck
was everyone?

805
01:03:32.600 --> 01:03:35.019
I got here!
Where the fuck were you?

806
01:03:35.061 --> 01:03:37.688
We don't know.
We don't have any evidence
of what went down here.

807
01:03:37.730 --> 01:03:39.690
I saw him. I told you.
It was him.

808
01:03:39.732 --> 01:03:41.901
I mean. you do realize
we're fielding something like

809
01:03:41.943 --> 01:03:43.736
two dozen bogus leads
by the hour?

810
01:03:43.778 --> 01:03:45.029
Just listen to me.

811
01:03:45.071 --> 01:03:46.405
Twenty years ago.

812
01:03:46.447 --> 01:03:48.199
devil-worshipper
Richard Joshua Reeves

813
01:03:48.241 --> 01:03:50.576
committed the church killings
in Harrisburg.

814
01:03:50.618 --> 01:03:53.246
A few years later. the satanic
metal band Demon Fist

815
01:03:53.287 --> 01:03:56.541
started writing songs
about Reeves inspired by him.

816
01:03:56.582 --> 01:03:58.668
They even posed
for one of their album covers

817
01:03:58.709 --> 01:04:01.170
in front of
the abandoned church
where the murders took place.

818
01:04:01.212 --> 01:04:02.630
Now. because of Reeves.

819
01:04:02.672 --> 01:04:04.465
and probably
because of those albums.

820
01:04:04.507 --> 01:04:07.301
that church.
Christ Cross Church.

821
01:04:07.343 --> 01:04:10.012
is a mecca
for would-be satanists.

822
01:04:10.054 --> 01:04:11.556
Reeves inspires Demon Fist.

823
01:04:11.597 --> 01:04:13.683
Demon Fist and Reeves
inspire the Slasher.

824
01:04:13.724 --> 01:04:17.353
He is quoting titles
and lyrics from these albums.

825
01:04:17.395 --> 01:04:18.729
And the whole time.

826
01:04:18.771 --> 01:04:20.648
the Slasher
is using Reeves's name.

827
01:04:20.690 --> 01:04:22.942
maybe even thinks he is Reeves.

828
01:04:22.984 --> 01:04:25.403
I'm telling you. the psycho
wants to finish it there.

829
01:04:26.487 --> 01:04:28.739
The Slasher
is going to Harrisburg.

830
01:04:28.781 --> 01:04:30.825
[reporter] In other news
outside the Slasher killings.

831
01:04:30.867 --> 01:04:32.577
today marks
the 28th anniversary

832
01:04:32.618 --> 01:04:34.579
of Three Mile Island.

833
01:04:34.620 --> 01:04:36.956
the worst civilian nuclear
disaster in American history.

834
01:04:37.790 --> 01:04:39.876
[man on radio] We were
outside early that morning.

835
01:04:39.917 --> 01:04:41.377
March 28th.

836
01:04:41.419 --> 01:04:42.879
And the ground
started to shake.

837
01:04:42.920 --> 01:04:44.672
My sister says.
"That's an earthquake."

838
01:04:44.714 --> 01:04:47.174
And I said. "It don't feel
like an earthquake.

839
01:04:47.216 --> 01:04:49.385
An earthquake. it don't
make sounds like that."

840
01:04:49.427 --> 01:04:52.138
I said.
"I think something happened
at Three Mile Island."

841
01:05:25.922 --> 01:05:28.382
[man 2 on radio]
They told us we had to
evacuate our homes immediately

842
01:05:28.424 --> 01:05:31.218
before a hole got burned down
to the center of the Earth.

843
01:05:31.260 --> 01:05:33.971
We abandoned everything.
Our homes. our belongings.

844
01:05:34.013 --> 01:05:35.848
We were terrified.

845
01:05:35.890 --> 01:05:37.850
[man 3 on radio] Well.
since we're on the subject.

846
01:05:37.892 --> 01:05:40.102
I firmly believe that it's
important to remember history.

847
01:05:40.144 --> 01:05:41.812
even if it's dark
or unpleasant.

848
01:05:41.854 --> 01:05:44.357
Maybe especially
if it's dark and unpleasant.

849
01:05:44.398 --> 01:05:46.484
because we have to learn
from our mistakes.

850
01:05:46.525 --> 01:05:48.235
[woman on radio]
I'm not arguing with that.

851
01:05:48.277 --> 01:05:50.780
but sometimes
we just have to let things go.

852
01:05:50.821 --> 01:05:52.490
[heavy breathing]

853
01:05:53.699 --> 01:05:55.409
[garage door creaking]

854
01:05:58.496 --> 01:06:00.289
[heavy breathing continues]

855
01:06:13.260 --> 01:06:14.720
[passenger door slams]

856
01:06:14.762 --> 01:06:16.263
So. why don't you call her
and find out?

857
01:06:16.305 --> 01:06:17.723
She's your sister. isn't she?

858
01:06:18.683 --> 01:06:19.809
If she's my sister.

859
01:06:19.850 --> 01:06:21.352
that makes her your sister too.

860
01:06:21.394 --> 01:06:23.145
I'm aware. I'm well aware.

861
01:06:23.187 --> 01:06:24.897
-Leonard Wilkes.
-Oh. fuck!

862
01:06:24.939 --> 01:06:26.107
[both panting]

863
01:06:28.359 --> 01:06:29.986
Do you love your wife?

864
01:06:38.202 --> 01:06:41.497
Well. look who finally decided
to show up.

865
01:06:47.795 --> 01:06:49.505
But where are you?

866
01:06:50.881 --> 01:06:52.299
[exhales]

867
01:07:13.487 --> 01:07:15.531
[♪ tense music playing]

868
01:07:21.078 --> 01:07:23.247
"3M1.

869
01:07:23.289 --> 01:07:25.207
3MI."

870
01:08:04.121 --> 01:08:06.582
[woman on radio] Today marks
the March 28th anniversary

871
01:08:06.624 --> 01:08:08.626
of Three Mile Island.

872
01:08:08.667 --> 01:08:11.670
the worst civilian nuclear
disaster in American history.

873
01:08:15.424 --> 01:08:17.426
[Jane] What did he want
from a public library?

874
01:08:18.177 --> 01:08:20.679
[Becky] He took exactly
two books. "N" and "T."

875
01:08:21.889 --> 01:08:23.140
[reporter]
...when the uranium core

876
01:08:23.182 --> 01:08:24.558
of the Harrisburg power plant

877
01:08:24.600 --> 01:08:26.185
partially melted down.

878
01:08:26.227 --> 01:08:29.021
spewing radiation
over Pennsylvania

879
01:08:29.063 --> 01:08:30.481
and neighboring states.

880
01:08:31.065 --> 01:08:33.317
A quantity of explosives
was stolen.

881
01:08:33.359 --> 01:08:35.945
Old-school. volatile TNT.

882
01:08:35.986 --> 01:08:40.157
[man 2 on radio]
They told us we had to
evacuate our homes immediately.

883
01:08:40.199 --> 01:08:43.911
before a hole got burned down
to the center of the Earth.

884
01:08:45.329 --> 01:08:46.831
Oh. my God.

885
01:08:49.708 --> 01:08:51.043
[tires screeching]

886
01:09:03.514 --> 01:09:06.600
[♪ ominous music playing]

887
01:09:13.440 --> 01:09:15.651
Christ. Leo.
Didn't you work already?

888
01:09:16.110 --> 01:09:17.319
[Leonard sighs]

889
01:09:17.820 --> 01:09:20.156
Just got called back in
by Kreiger. so it's. uh...

890
01:09:20.197 --> 01:09:21.949
It's urgent. so...
[clears throat]

891
01:09:23.033 --> 01:09:24.076
Yeah.

892
01:09:26.787 --> 01:09:27.955
Pop the back.

893
01:09:30.708 --> 01:09:33.043
Hurry up. Come on. Let's go.
You know the drill.

894
01:09:35.796 --> 01:09:36.881
[car trunk shuts]

895
01:09:37.590 --> 01:09:38.966
All right. let him through.

896
01:09:39.592 --> 01:09:40.718
[gate buzzes]

897
01:09:40.759 --> 01:09:42.094
[door mechanisms whirring]

898
01:09:54.315 --> 01:09:55.357
[breathing heavily]

899
01:09:55.399 --> 01:09:56.984
We're almost there. Please.

900
01:09:59.653 --> 01:10:01.030
[whimpering]

901
01:10:02.531 --> 01:10:04.325
[Slasher] Keep going.

902
01:10:04.366 --> 01:10:06.160
[siren wailing]

903
01:10:06.202 --> 01:10:08.454
This is not a joke. You need
to send officers right away.

904
01:10:08.495 --> 01:10:10.206
Do you understand?

905
01:10:10.247 --> 01:10:11.999
There's going to be an attack
on Three Mile Island.

906
01:10:18.964 --> 01:10:20.966
[Leonard's wife whimpering]

907
01:10:21.008 --> 01:10:23.385
-[Leonard] I'm sorry. honey.
-[whimpering]

908
01:10:23.427 --> 01:10:24.720
[Leonard] I'm so sorry.

909
01:10:25.304 --> 01:10:26.889
You'll be okay. okay?

910
01:10:26.931 --> 01:10:28.599
I'll be back. I promise. okay?
You'll be okay.

911
01:10:29.099 --> 01:10:30.601
I love you. I'll be back.

912
01:10:31.101 --> 01:10:34.146
[grunting] No. no. Please. No.

913
01:10:34.188 --> 01:10:35.522
Please.

914
01:10:35.564 --> 01:10:37.608
No. please. Please. Please.

915
01:10:37.650 --> 01:10:39.151
[groans]

916
01:10:39.193 --> 01:10:40.527
Please. Please.
you don't need me anymore.

917
01:10:40.569 --> 01:10:42.363
-[beeps]
-You can let me go.

918
01:10:42.863 --> 01:10:44.240
You don't have to do this.

919
01:10:45.366 --> 01:10:46.408
Just let me go.

920
01:10:51.205 --> 01:10:52.539
[Leonard] No. no. no.

921
01:10:53.540 --> 01:10:55.376
[panting]

922
01:10:56.043 --> 01:11:00.839
[Slasher] How you help me now
decides who lives or dies.

923
01:11:01.882 --> 01:11:03.008
[chattering]

924
01:11:05.594 --> 01:11:06.762
[muffled explosion]

925
01:11:09.598 --> 01:11:10.808
[tires screech]

926
01:11:13.435 --> 01:11:15.521
I'm Highway Patrol Officer
Jane Archer.

927
01:11:15.562 --> 01:11:17.606
Listen to me.
I have every reason to believe

928
01:11:17.648 --> 01:11:19.858
there's about to be
an attack on this plant.

929
01:11:19.900 --> 01:11:20.985
What are you talking about?

930
01:11:21.026 --> 01:11:23.112
[alarm blaring]

931
01:11:23.153 --> 01:11:25.489
He's here. He's already here.

932
01:11:26.198 --> 01:11:27.616
[guard on radio]
There's something going on

933
01:11:27.658 --> 01:11:28.701
at control reactor one.

934
01:11:29.201 --> 01:11:30.786
Open the gates! Do it!

935
01:11:30.828 --> 01:11:32.663
-You. ride with me.
-Hold on. Just hold on.

936
01:11:32.705 --> 01:11:34.123
Look. I know who he is.

937
01:11:34.164 --> 01:11:36.583
I can help you stop him.
but we need to move.

938
01:11:36.625 --> 01:11:37.710
[alarm continues]

939
01:11:40.004 --> 01:11:41.005
Okay.

940
01:11:41.672 --> 01:11:43.841
Let us through. then
lock it down and call it in.

941
01:11:50.097 --> 01:11:51.432
[engine revs]

942
01:11:56.645 --> 01:11:58.522
-[alarm blaring]
-[whimpers]

943
01:12:00.733 --> 01:12:03.319
[Slasher breathing heavily]

944
01:12:08.490 --> 01:12:09.700
[workers clamoring]

945
01:12:12.619 --> 01:12:15.622
[Slasher breathing heavily]

946
01:12:16.123 --> 01:12:17.958
[Leonard grunts. groans]

947
01:12:21.253 --> 01:12:23.714
[workers exclaim]

948
01:12:23.756 --> 01:12:25.049
[workers whimpering]

949
01:12:27.926 --> 01:12:30.012
[Leonard grunts. groans]

950
01:12:30.054 --> 01:12:31.138
[clamoring]

951
01:12:34.475 --> 01:12:35.601
[Leonard groans]

952
01:12:35.642 --> 01:12:37.102
-[neck cracking]
-[alarm blaring]

953
01:12:38.562 --> 01:12:39.605
[Slasher] Get out.

954
01:12:39.646 --> 01:12:41.482
[workers clamoring]

955
01:12:45.277 --> 01:12:46.612
[siren wailing]

956
01:12:49.448 --> 01:12:50.532
[Mitch] Jesus!

957
01:12:58.248 --> 01:13:00.000
[officer] Come on.
Spread out. Go. go. go.

958
01:13:00.042 --> 01:13:01.710
[officer 2] I got your six.
Come on.

959
01:13:01.752 --> 01:13:03.420
-[officer 3] Let's go.
-[officer 4] We're in. Hup!

960
01:13:03.462 --> 01:13:04.838
-[officer 5] Move it. move it.
-[officer 6] Go. go. go.

961
01:13:05.297 --> 01:13:06.465
[security chief] On me. on me.

962
01:13:06.507 --> 01:13:08.008
-[officers chattering]
-Go!

963
01:13:17.684 --> 01:13:19.395
[officer] Watch it. Here we go.

964
01:13:25.317 --> 01:13:26.443
-[Mitch] Stay close.
-[Jane] Yeah.

965
01:13:29.738 --> 01:13:30.989
[security chief] Go. go. go.

966
01:13:31.031 --> 01:13:32.825
[officers whispering]

967
01:13:43.168 --> 01:13:45.045
[foreman] He's locked
in the control room.

968
01:13:45.087 --> 01:13:46.839
He's taken Leo hostage.

969
01:13:46.880 --> 01:13:49.258
I need this hallway. people.
Everyone. back the hell off.

970
01:13:49.299 --> 01:13:51.677
Anyone from operations
or engineering. follow me.

971
01:14:03.397 --> 01:14:04.982
[unit powering up]

972
01:14:05.023 --> 01:14:07.693
[humming. clicking]

973
01:14:07.818 --> 01:14:09.820
[alarm ringing]

974
01:14:17.119 --> 01:14:19.163
[Slasher]
Do this one last thing.

975
01:14:20.122 --> 01:14:21.540
and I'll let you out.

976
01:14:22.916 --> 01:14:24.543
Your wife's waiting for you.

977
01:14:24.585 --> 01:14:25.919
[Leonard sobbing]

978
01:14:25.961 --> 01:14:28.297
[Slasher] Or don't do it.

979
01:14:28.338 --> 01:14:29.923
And I'll kill you.

980
01:14:32.801 --> 01:14:34.303
What have we got?

981
01:14:34.344 --> 01:14:36.096
[engineer]
Reactor one's operating at 75%.

982
01:14:36.138 --> 01:14:38.015
The problem is
Leo's flushing the core.

983
01:14:38.056 --> 01:14:39.349
He overrode the system. He's...

984
01:14:39.391 --> 01:14:41.351
He's purging the coolant.
All of it.

985
01:14:41.393 --> 01:14:42.895
[engineer 2]
Water levels are plummeting.

986
01:14:42.936 --> 01:14:44.396
[foreman] The emergency system
will kick in

987
01:14:44.438 --> 01:14:45.939
once the core temperature
rises above nominal.

988
01:14:45.981 --> 01:14:48.650
He's gonna kill that man. Leo.

989
01:14:49.276 --> 01:14:50.611
This isn't a hostage situation.

990
01:14:50.652 --> 01:14:52.446
There's not gonna be
a negotiation.

991
01:14:52.488 --> 01:14:53.989
Look. I know how this sounds.

992
01:14:54.031 --> 01:14:55.991
but the guy in there.
that's the Slasher.

993
01:14:56.033 --> 01:14:58.827
I've been following him.
and this has been his plan
all along.

994
01:14:58.869 --> 01:15:00.454
His suicide.

995
01:15:01.538 --> 01:15:02.581
[breathes shakily]

996
01:15:02.623 --> 01:15:03.874
[clunking]

997
01:15:03.916 --> 01:15:05.918
[alarms blaring]

998
01:15:16.678 --> 01:15:18.222
[Jane] He's very dangerous.

999
01:15:18.263 --> 01:15:19.806
He has explosives.
He will have brought them.

1000
01:15:20.516 --> 01:15:23.936
[engineer 2] If he blows up
the IC system. we're done.

1001
01:15:27.564 --> 01:15:29.149
[alarm continues]

1002
01:15:35.948 --> 01:15:37.032
[Leonard whimpering]

1003
01:15:40.536 --> 01:15:42.663
No. no. no. Please. no.

1004
01:15:42.704 --> 01:15:44.248
Please. please. please.

1005
01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:48.043
[muffled gunshot]

1006
01:16:19.700 --> 01:16:21.660
He's gonna use the grenade
as a detonator.

1007
01:16:21.702 --> 01:16:23.579
That much TNT... [stammers]

1008
01:16:23.620 --> 01:16:25.789
It can take out
the entire control room.

1009
01:16:25.831 --> 01:16:28.250
Well. can't you just shut it
down before he does anything?

1010
01:16:28.292 --> 01:16:29.626
You must be able to do that.

1011
01:16:29.668 --> 01:16:30.711
Not from outside
the control room. no.

1012
01:16:30.752 --> 01:16:34.006
[Slasher breathing heavily]

1013
01:16:40.387 --> 01:16:42.180
-[knife thuds]
-[grunts]

1014
01:16:51.898 --> 01:16:53.567
He's gonna fucking
melt us down.

1015
01:16:53.609 --> 01:16:55.319
[alarm buzzing]

1016
01:16:55.360 --> 01:16:56.862
[foreman] He's gonna take out
a city full of people.

1017
01:16:56.903 --> 01:16:58.572
[engineer] More like
the entire East Coast.

1018
01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:09.499
Security.

1019
01:17:09.541 --> 01:17:11.168
you've got to get in there
right now.

1020
01:17:11.209 --> 01:17:13.170
You have to get in there
and stop him.

1021
01:17:14.338 --> 01:17:15.589
Is there another way
into the control room?

1022
01:17:15.631 --> 01:17:17.007
The ventilation system?

1023
01:17:17.049 --> 01:17:18.759
It's secure.
That's the whole point.

1024
01:17:18.800 --> 01:17:20.594
It's even designed
to keep a radiation leak out.

1025
01:17:20.636 --> 01:17:21.970
[foreman] All right. people.
Listen up.

1026
01:17:22.012 --> 01:17:24.222
Notify the NRC
and Civil Defense.

1027
01:17:24.264 --> 01:17:27.434
Tell them Three Mile Island
is on the verge
of catastrophic failure.

1028
01:17:27.976 --> 01:17:31.146
If we're lucky. they've got
two. maybe three hours

1029
01:17:31.188 --> 01:17:33.523
to try to evacuate
all of central Pennsylvania.

1030
01:17:35.609 --> 01:17:37.319
[beeping]

1031
01:17:38.904 --> 01:17:40.697
There might be a way. Come on.

1032
01:17:43.742 --> 01:17:45.786
[♪ tense music playing]

1033
01:18:11.603 --> 01:18:13.772
This has been closed since...
[exhales] ...forever.

1034
01:18:13.814 --> 01:18:14.856
[lock clicks]

1035
01:18:20.237 --> 01:18:21.279
It's plexi.

1036
01:18:21.321 --> 01:18:22.406
It's bulletproof. I'm sure.

1037
01:18:24.074 --> 01:18:25.742
[♪ ominous music playing]

1038
01:18:48.473 --> 01:18:50.183
[no audible dialogue]

1039
01:18:50.225 --> 01:18:51.601
[Jane] Stop!

1040
01:18:51.643 --> 01:18:52.978
Hey!

1041
01:18:53.019 --> 01:18:55.021
[yells]

1042
01:18:55.063 --> 01:18:56.189
[panting]

1043
01:18:56.231 --> 01:18:58.150
It's over. There's no way. I...

1044
01:19:01.153 --> 01:19:02.738
Sorry. but fuck this.

1045
01:19:08.118 --> 01:19:10.078
[Slasher] Hail Satan!

1046
01:19:10.120 --> 01:19:13.206
Welcome your servant
into the kingdom of hell.

1047
01:19:13.248 --> 01:19:15.000
[whimpers]

1048
01:19:17.544 --> 01:19:18.503
[beeping]

1049
01:19:25.218 --> 01:19:27.304
-[objects clatter]
-[panting]

1050
01:19:34.478 --> 01:19:35.729
[muffled gunfire]

1051
01:19:38.899 --> 01:19:42.194
[Slasher] All in your name.
Almighty Diabolus.

1052
01:19:56.291 --> 01:19:57.584
[breathing heavily]

1053
01:19:59.085 --> 01:20:00.879
[Slasher] Open the gates!

1054
01:20:02.088 --> 01:20:03.256
-[gunshot]
-[Slasher groans]

1055
01:20:47.717 --> 01:20:50.345
Go to hell. psycho.

1056
01:20:54.224 --> 01:20:55.642
[gunshot]

1057
01:21:15.579 --> 01:21:16.621
[sighs]

1058
01:21:24.129 --> 01:21:25.881
[male news anchor] Authorities
are remaining tight-lipped

1059
01:21:25.922 --> 01:21:27.966
about the status
of the investigation.

1060
01:21:28.008 --> 01:21:29.968
[female news anchor] Why are
there Satanic Slashers?

1061
01:21:30.010 --> 01:21:32.637
Is it Richard Joshua Reeves?

1062
01:21:32.679 --> 01:21:34.723
[male news anchor 2]
There's no doubt in my mind

1063
01:21:34.764 --> 01:21:37.893
that the
Three Mile Island killer
is in fact The Satanic Slasher.

1064
01:21:37.934 --> 01:21:39.728
[female news anchor 2] There
is speculation over whether

1065
01:21:39.769 --> 01:21:42.522
the Three Mile Island killer
may still be alive.

1066
01:21:42.564 --> 01:21:44.190
[woman] See. I told you.

1067
01:21:44.232 --> 01:21:45.817
Our government
is creating human monsters

1068
01:21:45.859 --> 01:21:47.444
and releasing them
back into the world.

1069
01:21:47.485 --> 01:21:49.821
[overlapping news reports
continue]

1070
01:21:49.863 --> 01:21:51.573
[female news anchor 3]
Shown here on archival footage

1071
01:21:51.615 --> 01:21:54.534
is Richard Joshua Reeves's
1999 arrest

1072
01:21:54.576 --> 01:21:56.912
and conviction for
the Christ Cross mass murder.

1073
01:21:56.953 --> 01:21:59.456
which was thought to
have brought an end
to his killing spree.

1074
01:21:59.497 --> 01:22:01.541
That tragedy now
pales in comparison

1075
01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:03.627
to the trail of death
he left in his wake

1076
01:22:03.668 --> 01:22:06.338
in the past few weeks
as The Satanic Slasher.

1077
01:22:12.177 --> 01:22:15.055
[female news anchor 3]
At a minimum.
he is responsible for 48 deaths

1078
01:22:15.096 --> 01:22:16.723
on his recent murder spree.

1079
01:22:16.765 --> 01:22:18.767
And some claim
that he may have survived

1080
01:22:18.808 --> 01:22:21.186
his suicide run
at Three Mile Island.

1081
01:22:22.187 --> 01:22:25.315
A spokesperson for the FBI
denies those claims.

1082
01:22:25.357 --> 01:22:27.692
insisting Reeves suffered
several gunshot wounds

1083
01:22:27.734 --> 01:22:31.988
including one to the head.
which ultimately proved fatal.

1084
01:22:32.030 --> 01:22:33.573
[birds chirping]

1085
01:23:11.987 --> 01:23:13.071
[grunts]

1086
01:23:13.113 --> 01:23:15.156
[♪ ominous music playing]

1087
01:23:44.519 --> 01:23:46.146
[Jane panting]

1088
01:23:52.819 --> 01:23:54.863
[sighs]

1089
01:24:08.084 --> 01:24:09.961
[man] Welcome home. Reeves.

1090
01:24:10.003 --> 01:24:12.172
[man 2] Yeah.
Death Valley missed you.

1091
01:24:12.213 --> 01:24:15.091
[man laughing]

1092
01:24:16.342 --> 01:24:18.762
[♪ metal music playing.
3TEETH "Merchant of the Void"]

1093
01:24:49.292 --> 01:24:51.044
[song continues]

1094
01:27:23.947 --> 01:27:25.615
[song ends]

1095
01:27:27.075 --> 01:27:29.285
[♪ ominous music playing]

1096
01:31:03.666 --> 01:31:05.042
[music ends]

1096
